
The Smashing Pumpkins are currently in the recording studio with Baker at work
on their first new album since 2000.[1]

Although he now spends much of his time at his studio in Arizona, Baker got his start at Decca Records in England at the age
of 14. Later he moved to Trident Studios, where he worked with people such as Gus Dudgeon
and Tony Visconti.

Albums co-produced by Roy Thomas Baker:
Roy Thomas Baker is an English record producer who helped create a number of
extremely popular pop and rock records in the 1970s and 1980s. Perhaps best known for co-producing the enduring hit song
"Bohemian Rhapsody" for Queen, he also worked
with numerous, notable artists, including Guns N' Roses, The
Who, The Rolling Stones, David Bowie,
The Cars, Foreigner, Journey, Ozzy Osbourne, T.
Rex, Devo, The Stranglers, Dusty Springfield, Starcastle, Yes, Cheap Trick and Gasolin'. His
most recent production work was for The Darkness' 2005 album "One Way Ticket to Hell... and
Back".